Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: Products.WebServerAuth
Version: 1.3.1
Summary: Delegates Plone's authentication concerns to a web server
Home-page: http://plone.org/products/webserverauth
Author: Erik Rose
Author-email: support@weblion.psu.edu
License: GPL
Description: WebServerAuth allows Plone to delegate authentication concerns to a web server like Apache or IIS. Using WebServerAuth, Plone can be configured so any user known to your LDAP, Kerberos, Shibboleth, or Pubcookie system (or any other system for which your web server has an authentication module) can transparently log in using enterprise-wide credentials.
        
        `Read more at the WebServerAuth product page... <http://plone.org/products/webserverauth/>`_
        
